doc.after: "Collige, virgo, rosas" ("gather, girl, the roses") appears at the end of the poem "De rosis nascentibus"[7] ("Of growing roses", also called Idyllium de rosis) attributed to Ausonius or Virgil. It encourages youth to enjoy life before it is too late; compare "Gather ye rosebuds while ye may" from "To the Virgins, to Make Much of Time".
